apertium-anaphora
------------------------------------------
Anaphora Resolution Module in Apertium for low resource languages

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3
  cygwin-3.4.3-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libicu70-70.1-1
  liblttoolbox3-3.7.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libxml2-2.9.12-2
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.35.5-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libicu-devel-70.1-1
  liblttoolbox-devel-3.7.1-1bl1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.12-2
  make-4.4-1
  utf8cpp-3.2.1-1bl1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/apertium/apertium-anaphora

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/apertium/apertium-anaphora/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack apertium-anaphora-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./apertium-anaphora-1.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/apertium-anaphora-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/apertium-anaphora-1.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(apertium-anaphora)
  /usr/bin/apertium-anaphora.exe
  /usr/bin/apertium-validate-anaphora
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/apertium-anaphora.pc
  /usr/share/apertium-anaphora/anaphora.dtd
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/apertium-anaphora.README
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-anaphora/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-anaphora/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-anaphora/README
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-anaphora/readme.md

